The paper discusses the design of a "COllective INtelligence" (COIN) system, which involves multiple agents running reinforcement learning algorithms to optimize a world utility function. This topic falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), specifically in the sub-categories of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also touches on the social implications of COINs, which relates to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions game theory (cs.GT) as a related field that could benefit from insights gained through COIN research.
